modules.description: Manages WebSocket-based subscription states with operations to add, remove, and track active subscriptions. Works with custom subscription types and WebSocket connections to handle real-time event routing. Used to coordinate live data streams between clients and backend services over persistent connections.

This module handles incoming WebSocket messages for GraphQL subscriptions, parsing and routing them to the correct callbacks while managing subscription states and streaming results over persistent connections. It works with GraphQL variables, WebSocket data frames, and result handlers, offering operations to register subscriptions, process messages, and manage active streams. The child module extends this by tracking and coordinating live subscription states, allowing clients to maintain and terminate real-time data flows with custom subscription types. Together, they enable a GraphQL server to support reactive, bidirectional communication over WebSockets for events like live updates and streaming queries.
